            . I live in Crown-street; I am a <rs id="t18320906-392-viclabel2208" type="occupation">hair-dresser</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18320906-392-victim3201 t18320906-392-viclabel2208"></join>. The prisoner was occasionally employed in my shop, and was so about one month before the 4th of September; I left fifteen razors in my shop on the 31st of August, and missed four - the next morning I went to the prisoner's shop, in Holywell-lane - I asked what he came to my shop for; he said to sell a couple of boards, which we generally hang outside our doors, and I asked him about the razors - he said he knew nothing about them, but one which my boy took from him.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18320906-392-person3203">
